SIMPLE: turbinated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turbinated
<hw>Tur"bi*na`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>turbinatus</ets>, fr.
<ets>turbo</ets>, <ets>turben</ets>, <ets>turbinis</ets>, a whirl,
top.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Whirling in the manner of a top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A spiral and <qex>turbinated</qex> motion of the whole.</q>
<rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Shaped like a top, or inverted
cone; narrow at the base, and broad at the apex; <as>as, a
<ex>turbinated</ex> ovary, pericarp, or root</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Turbinal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Spiral with the whorls decreasing
rapidly from a large base to a pointed apex; -- said of certain
shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turbination</ent>⟦br⟧
